</style></head><body><p class="s1" style="padding-top: 6pt;padding-left: 6pt;text-indent: 0pt;text-align: left;">Ross Money</p><p style="padding-top: 15pt;padding-left: 31pt;text-indent: 0pt;text-align: left;"><a href="https://github.com/rossmoney">https://github.com/rossmoney</a></p><p style="text-indent: 0pt;text-align: left;"><br/></p><h1 style="padding-left: 6pt;text-indent: 0pt;text-align: left;">Summary</h1><p style="padding-top: 3pt;padding-left: 6pt;text-indent: 0pt;line-height: 122%;text-align: left;">I have over four years of experience in web development, using frameworks such as Laravel and Vue.js. I am also starting out as a DevOps Developer with knowledge of AWS Cloud and Infrastructure as Code tools.</p><p style="text-indent: 0pt;text-align: left;"><br/></p><p style="padding-left: 6pt;text-indent: 0pt;line-height: 122%;text-align: left;">I am passionate about creating efficient, reliable, and user-friendly solutions that meet the needs and expectations of the clients and the users.</p><h1 style="padding-top: 8pt;padding-left: 6pt;text-indent: 0pt;text-align: left;">Experience</h1><p class="s2" style="padding-top: 7pt;padding-left: 5pt;text-indent: 0pt;line-height: 18pt;text-align: left;"><span><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td><img width="24" height="24" src="data:image/jpg;base64,"/></td></tr></table></span> <span class="h2">PHP Developer (DevOps)</span></p><p class="s3" style="padding-left: 28pt;text-indent: 0pt;line-height: 14pt;text-align: left;">Rawnet Digital Agency</p><p style="padding-top: 2pt;padding-left: 28pt;text-indent: 0pt;text-align: left;">Oct 2021 - Apr 2024 (2 years 7 months)</p><p style="padding-top: 2pt;padding-left: 28pt;text-indent: 0pt;line-height: 122%;text-align: left;">Working as DevOps support / PHP developer for our in-house developers and supporting our senior DevOps engineer with infrastructure builds and updates on AWS, following AWS well-architected framework and using Terraform and Ansible.</p><p style="text-indent: 0pt;text-align: left;"><br/></p><ul id="l1"><li data-list-text="-"><p style="padding-left: 34pt;text-indent: -6pt;text-align: left;">Monitoring uptime and resilience of our client sites and reporting on server downtime.</p></li><li data-list-text="-"><p style="padding-top: 2pt;padding-left: 34pt;text-indent: -6pt;text-align: left;">Wrote and maintained bespoke developer tooling using Golang.</p></li><li data-list-text="-"><p style="padding-top: 2pt;padding-left: 34pt;text-indent: -6pt;text-align: left;">Patch management and installation of packages on Ubuntu Servers using Canonical Landscape.</p></li><li data-list-text="-"><p style="padding-top: 2pt;padding-left: 34pt;text-indent: -6pt;text-align: left;">Developing PHP code for Concrete5 CMS.</p></li><li data-list-text="-"><p style="padding-top: 2pt;padding-left: 34pt;text-indent: -6pt;text-align: left;">Actioning SSL certificate renewals within AWS ACM.</p></li><li data-list-text="-"><p style="padding-top: 2pt;padding-left: 34pt;text-indent: -6pt;text-align: left;">Supporting local Docker setups for each project including Makefile commands.</p></li><li data-list-text="-"><p style="padding-top: 2pt;padding-left: 34pt;text-indent: -6pt;text-align: left;">Acted as a point of contact for other developers for AWS queries and support.</p></li><li data-list-text="-"><p style="padding-top: 2pt;padding-left: 28pt;text-indent: 0pt;line-height: 122%;text-align: left;">Maintained robust security measures, including IP blocking through AWS Web Application Firewall, as well as monitoring container and dependency scans in Gitlab.</p><p style="text-indent: 0pt;text-align: left;"><br/></p><p style="text-indent: 0pt;text-align: left;"><span><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td><img width="24" height="8" src="data:image/jpg;base64,"/></td></tr></table></span></p><h2 style="padding-top: 4pt;padding-left: 28pt;text-indent: 0pt;text-align: left;">Developer</h2><p class="s3" style="padding-top: 3pt;padding-left: 28pt;text-indent: 0pt;text-align: left;">Project Better Energy</p><p style="padding-top: 3pt;padding-left: 28pt;text-indent: 0pt;text-align: left;">Apr 2018 - Sep 2021 (3 years 6 months)</p><p style="padding-top: 2pt;padding-left: 28pt;text-indent: 0pt;line-height: 122%;text-align: left;">Collaborated within a team of 4 developers and one QA Tester, utilizing Git for version control and Gitlab issue tracker.</p><p style="text-indent: 0pt;text-align: left;"><br/></p></li><li data-list-text="-"><p style="padding-left: 28pt;text-indent: 0pt;line-height: 122%;text-align: left;">Contributed to maintaining and developing diverse web-based (Laravel) applications managing various aspects of business operations (CMS, Sales, IT Support, Recruitment) for different brands and products, and linking together business operations with different applications.</p></li><li data-list-text="-"><p style="padding-left: 28pt;text-indent: 0pt;line-height: 122%;text-align: left;">Developed finance application screens for the main sales app to support new finance companies / integrations, and utilising each companies specific API to register the finance.</p></li><li data-list-text="-"><p style="padding-left: 28pt;text-indent: 0pt;line-height: 122%;text-align: left;">Executed frontend work, transforming designs from in-house and external agencies into web-based products using Reveal.js presentation framework, Illustrator, and Photoshop.</p></li><li data-list-text="-"><p style="padding-left: 28pt;text-indent: 0pt;line-height: 122%;text-align: left;">Contributed to the implementation of features for listing stockists of EV Chargers, which were incorporated into a map on the front-facing web.</p><p style="text-indent: 0pt;text-align: left;"><br/></p><p style="text-indent: 0pt;text-align: left;"><span><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td><img width="24" height="24" src="data:image/jpg;base64,"/></td></tr></table></span></p><h2 style="padding-top: 4pt;padding-left: 28pt;text-indent: 0pt;text-align: left;">Web Developer</h2><p class="s3" style="padding-top: 5pt;padding-left: 28pt;text-indent: 0pt;text-align: left;">Regit</p><p style="padding-top: 2pt;padding-left: 28pt;text-indent: 0pt;text-align: left;">Sep 2016 - Apr 2018 (1 year 8 months)</p><p style="padding-top: 2pt;padding-left: 28pt;text-indent: 0pt;line-height: 122%;text-align: left;"><a href="http://www.regit.cars/" class="s4" target="_blank">Team of 6 developers utilising the agile philosophy with Pivotal task tracker. https://www.regit.cars</a></p><p style="text-indent: 0pt;text-align: left;"><br/></p></li><li data-list-text="-"><p style="padding-left: 28pt;text-indent: 0pt;line-height: 122%;text-align: left;">Building new software for the in-house call centre utilising Laravel, Vue JS and Twilio. This integrated platform allowed sales people to track leads and directly start a call, improving efficiency.</p></li><li data-list-text="-"><p style="padding-left: 28pt;text-indent: 0pt;line-height: 122%;text-align: left;">Building new features for the motoring.co.uk website rebrand. Utilising access to APIs providing official data on vehicles queried using Reg numbers. Rebrand helped drive more people to the company.</p><p style="text-indent: 0pt;text-align: left;"><br/></p><p class="s2" style="padding-top: 4pt;padding-left: 5pt;text-indent: 0pt;line-height: 18pt;text-align: left;"><span><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td><img width="24" height="24" src="data:image/jpg;base64,"/></td></tr></table></span> <span class="h2">Travelling</span></p><p class="s3" style="padding-left: 28pt;text-indent: 0pt;line-height: 14pt;text-align: left;">Travelling</p><p style="padding-top: 2pt;padding-left: 28pt;text-indent: 0pt;text-align: left;">Dec 2015 - Aug 2016 (9 months)</p><p style="text-indent: 0pt;text-align: left;"><br/></p><p class="s2" style="padding-top: 10pt;padding-left: 5pt;text-indent: 0pt;line-height: 18pt;text-align: left;"><span><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td><img width="24" height="24" src="data:image/jpg;base64,"/></td></tr></table></span> <span class="h2">LAMP PHP Developer</span></p><p class="s3" style="padding-left: 28pt;text-indent: 0pt;line-height: 14pt;text-align: left;">FusePump</p><p style="padding-top: 2pt;padding-left: 28pt;text-indent: 0pt;text-align: left;">Jan 2014 - Nov 2015 (1 year 11 months)</p><p style="padding-top: 2pt;padding-left: 28pt;text-indent: 0pt;line-height: 122%;text-align: left;">Affiliate marketing focus through the use of data scraping technology working to directly increase client sales on the web.</p><p style="text-indent: 0pt;text-align: left;"><br/></p><p style="padding-left: 28pt;text-indent: 0pt;text-align: left;">Utilisation of JIRA and the AGILE methodology with daily stand-ups, 8 developer team.</p><p style="text-indent: 0pt;text-align: left;"><br/></p></li><li data-list-text="-"><p style="padding-left: 28pt;text-indent: 0pt;line-height: 122%;text-align: left;">Supporting the &quot;BuyNow&quot; solution, (now absorbed under WPP agency), by building agents to scrape price and other metadata related to the products to store in a MySQL database.</p></li><li data-list-text="-"><p style="padding-left: 34pt;text-indent: -6pt;line-height: 11pt;text-align: left;">Worked on in-house systems for clients to set up the scrapes and manage their reach.</p></li><li data-list-text="-"><p style="padding-top: 2pt;padding-left: 34pt;text-indent: -6pt;text-align: left;">Utilised the Linux command line to run agents to test them under proprietary scraping framework.</p></li></ul><p style="text-indent: 0pt;text-align: left;"><br/></p><h1 style="padding-top: 4pt;padding-left: 6pt;text-indent: 0pt;text-align: left;">Education</h1><p class="s2" style="padding-top: 7pt;padding-left: 7pt;text-indent: 0pt;line-height: 17pt;text-align: left;"><span><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td><img width="16" height="20" src="data:image/jpg;base64,"/></td></tr></table></span> <span class="h2">University of Plymouth</span></p><p class="s3" style="padding-left: 28pt;text-indent: 0pt;line-height: 14pt;text-align: left;">BS, Computing</p><p style="padding-top: 2pt;padding-left: 28pt;text-indent: 0pt;text-align: left;">2010 - 2013</p><p style="text-indent: 0pt;text-align: left;"><br/></p><h1 style="padding-left: 6pt;text-indent: 0pt;text-align: left;">Licenses &amp; Certifications</h1><p class="s2" style="padding-top: 7pt;padding-left: 5pt;text-indent: 0pt;text-align: left;"><span><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td><img width="24" height="24" src="data:image/jpg;base64,"/></td></tr></table></span> <span class="h2">AWS Certified Cloud Practitioner </span><span class="s3">- Amazon Web Services (AWS)</span></p><h1 style="padding-top: 15pt;padding-left: 6pt;text-indent: 0pt;text-align: left;">Skills</h1><p style="padding-top: 3pt;padding-left: 12pt;text-indent: 0pt;line-height: 122%;text-align: left;">Concrete5 CMS • Go (Programming Language) • Docker • Ansible • DevOps • Amazon Web Services (AWS) • Terraform • PHP • Vue.js • Laravel</p></body></html>
